ID scheme\\n   - Updated database.py to support both old and new ID formats\\n   - Created migration scripts\\n   - Built an installation script to automate the entire process\\n\\n4. File Implementation Details:\\n   - fixed_id_generator.py: Core module for generating consistent IDs\\n   - update_custom_names.py: Updates mapping file with UUIDs to descriptive names\\n   - correct_duplicate_ids.py: Detects and fixes duplicate references\\n   - formatters_updated.py: Modified version of formatters.py\\n   - database_updated.py: Modified version of database.py\\n   - migrate_database.py: Migration script for existing data\\n   - install_updates.sh: Installation script\\n\\n5. Testing and Implementation:\\n   - The user had me run the installation script\\n   - We verified the implementation by checking the custom_project_names.json file\\n   - We examined the database after migration to confirm changes\\n\\n6. Results:\\n   - The system now uses consistent IDs based on UUIDs extracted from filenames\\n   - Multiple timestamp-based IDs for the same conversation were consolidated\\n   - The custom naming (like \\\"reestruturação\\\") was preserved\\n\\n7. Current Status:\\n   - The installation was successful\\n   - The solution has been fully implemented\\n   - The user's issue with inconsistent IDs has been resolved\\n</analysis>\\n\\n<summary>\\n1. Primary Request and Intent:\\n   The user was experiencing a problem with the LightRAG system where each time a conversation was referenced, it would generate a new ID based on a timestamp (format: doc_TIMESTAMP). This was causing inconsistency and confusion as the same conversation file would have different IDs each time it was mentioned. The user wanted a solution that would maintain a consistent ID for each conversation file, regardless of when it was accessed.\\n\\n2. Key Technical Concepts:\\n   - LightRAG: A Retrieval Augmented Generation system for managing and accessing conversation data\\n   - Document IDs: Unique identifiers for documents in the knowledge base\\n   - UUID extraction: Extracting Universal Unique Identifiers from conversation filenames\\n   - Custom name mappings: Persistent associations between IDs and descriptive names\\n   - Database migration: Converting existing entries to use the new ID format\\n   - Duplicate detection and consolidation: Finding and merging records that reference the same conversation\\n\\n3. Files and Code Sections:\\n   - `/Users/agents/.claude/lightrag/fixed_id_generator.py`\\n     - Core module for generating consistent IDs based on conversation UUIDs\\n     - Contains functions for UUID extraction, ID generation, and name registration\\n     - Key functions: `extract_uuid_from_filename()`, `generate_consistent_id()`, `register_document_name()`\\n     ```python\\n     def generate_consistent_id(filename: str) -> Tuple[str, str]:\\n         \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n         Gera um ID consistente baseado no UUID do arquivo .jsonl\\n         \\n         Args:\\n             filename: Nome do arquivo .jsonl\\n             \\n         Retorna:\\n             Tuple[str, str]: ID gerado e o nome descritivo do documento\\n         \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n         uuid = extract_uuid_from_filename(filename)\\n         \\n         if not uuid:\\n             # Fallback para timestamp se não encontrar UUID\\n             import datetime\\n             return f\\\"doc_{int(datetime.datetime.now().timestamp() * 1000)}\\\", filename\\n         \\n         # Gerar ID com prefixo conv_ para indicar que é uma conversa\\n         conv_id = f\\\"conv_{uuid}\\\"\\n         \\n         # Gerar nome descritivo\\n         display_name = f\\\"Conversa Claude: {uuid}.jsonl\\\"\\n         \\n         return conv_id, display_name\\n     ```\\n\\n   - `/Users/agents/.claude/lightrag/update_custom_names.py`\\n     - Script for updating the mapping file with UUIDs to descriptive names\\n     - Scans project directories for conversation files and generates mappings\\n     - Preserves existing mappings while adding new ones\\n\\n   - `/Users/agents/.claude/lightrag/correct_duplicate_ids.py`\\n     - Detects and fixes duplicate references to the same conversation\\n     - Consolidates multiple timestamp-based IDs into a single consistent ID\\n     - Preserves document content while updating reference information\\n\\n   - `/Users/agents/.claude/lightrag/utils/formatters_updated.py`\\n     - Modified version of the formatters module to use the new ID scheme\\n     - Adds support for displaying friendly names instead of raw IDs\\n     - Updates output formatting for various command results\\n\\n   - `/Users/agents/.claude/lightrag/core/database_updated.py`\\n     - Modified version of the database module to support both old and new ID formats\\n     - Updates document insertion logic to use consistent IDs for conversations\\n     - Adds support for querying by both original and new IDs\\n     ```python\\n     def insert_document(self, content: str, source: str = \\\"manual\\\", \\n                         summary: Optional[str] = None, \\n                         metadata: Optional[Dict] = None) -> Dict:\\n         \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n         Insere um novo documento na base de conhecimento\\n         \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n         # [...]\\n         \\n         # Determinar o tipo de documento e gerar ID apropriado\\n         doc_id = None\\n         display_name = None\\n         \\n         # Verificar se é uma conversa Claude (para conversas JSONL)\\n         if \\\".jsonl\\\" in source or \\\"Conversa Claude\\\" in (summary or \\\"\\\"):\\n             # Extrair UUID do nome do arquivo (source)\\n             conv_id, name = generate_consistent_id(source)\\n             doc_id = conv_id\\n             display_name = name\\n         else:\\n             # Gerar ID baseado em timestamp para outros tipos de documento\\n             doc_id = f\\\"doc_{int(datetime.datetime.now().timestamp() * 1000)}\\\"\\n             display_name = summary or \\\"Docume