rves existing mappings while adding new ones\\n\\n   - `/Users/agents/.claude/lightrag/correct_duplicate_ids.py`\\n     - Detects and fixes duplicate references to the same conversation\\n     - Consolidates multiple timestamp-based IDs into a single consistent ID\\n     - Preserves document content while updating reference information\\n\\n   - `/Users/agents/.claude/lightrag/utils/formatters_updated.py`\\n     - Modified version of the formatters module to use the new ID scheme\\n     - Adds support for displaying friendly names instead of raw IDs\\n     - Updates output formatting for various command results\\n\\n   - `/Users/agents/.claude/lightrag/core/database_updated.py`\\n     - Modified version of the database module to support both old and new ID formats\\n     - Updates document insertion logic to use consistent IDs for conversations\\n     - Adds support for querying by both original and new IDs\\n     ```python\\n     def insert_document(self, content: str, source: str = \\\"manual\\\", \\n                         summary: Optional[str] = None, \\n                         metadata: Optional[Dict] = None) -> Dict:\\n         \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n         Insere um novo documento na base de conhecimento\\n         \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n         # [...]\\n         \\n         # Determinar o tipo de documento e gerar ID apropriado\\n         doc_id = None\\n         display_name = None\\n         \\n         # Verificar se é uma conversa Claude (para conversas JSONL)\\n         if \\\".jsonl\\\" in source or \\\"Conversa Claude\\\" in (summary or \\\"\\\"):\\n             # Extrair UUID do nome do arquivo (source)\\n             conv_id, name = generate_consistent_id(source)\\n             doc_id = conv_id\\n             display_name = name\\n         else:\\n             # Gerar ID baseado em timestamp para outros tipos de documento\\n             doc_id = f\\\"doc_{int(datetime.datetime.now().timestamp() * 1000)}\\\"\\n             display_name = summary or \\\"Documento sem resumo\\\"\\n         \\n         # Registrar nome amigável\\n         register_document_name(doc_id, display_name)\\n         \\n         # [rest of the function...]\\n     ```\\n\\n   - `/Users/agents/.claude/lightrag/migrate_database.py`\\n     - Migration script for converting existing database entries to the new ID format\\n     - Analyzes document content to extract conversation UUIDs\\n     - Updates IDs while preserving associations with custom names\\n\\n   - `/Users/agents/.claude/lightrag/install_updates.sh`\\n     - Installation script that automates the entire update process\\n     - Backs up original files, installs new ones, and runs migration scripts\\n     - Provides user feedback during the installation process\\n\\n   - `/Users/agents/.claude/lightrag/README_ID_UPDATES.md`\\n     - Documentation explaining the changes, installation process, and usage\\n\\n4. Problem Solving:\\n   - Solved the issue of inconsistent IDs by implementing a UUID-based ID system\\n   - Addressed the challenge of maintaining custom names by preserving mappings during migration\\n   - Fixed the problem of duplicate entries by implementing detection and consolidation\\n   - Ensured backward compatibility by supporting both old and new ID formats\\n   - Made the solution user-friendly by automating the installation process\\n\\n5. Pending Tasks:\\n   - None currently. The solution has been fully implemented and tested.\\n\\n6. Current Work:\\n   We just completed the installation of the updated system by running the install_updates.sh script. The installation process:\\n   - Created backups of the original files\\n   - Updated the code files with the new implementations\\n   - Migrated the database to use the new ID format\\n   - Updated the mapping file with UUIDs to descriptive names\\n   - Consolidated duplicate entries\\n   \\n   The verification steps showed that:\\n   - The custom_project_names.json now contains mappings for both the old IDs and the new conv_U